Sodiq Oyeleke There was a fire outbreak at the popular Oba Market in Benin, Edo State. The PUNCH gathered that the fire started midnight and efforts to put it out are ongoing as of 09.00am on Monday. READ ALSO: APC, Edo set for showdown as gov primary holds today The cause of the fire was yet to be ascertained as of the time of filing this report. Federal Fire Service Zone K tweeted, “At about 1:00hrs this morning Men of Federal Fire Service Zone K Edo command turned out to combat a raging inferno at Oba market ring road Benin city Edo State. In attendance are Nigerian Army, Nigerian Air force, NPDC, and UNIBEN fire service.” Details later…